---
import TopicLayout from '../../layouts/TopicLayout.astro';

const title = "Verlan Tools & Resources";
const description = "Interactive tools for learning French verlan: translators, quizzes, pronunciation guides, and practical learning resources.";

const relatedTopics = [
  { title: "Overview", url: "/verlan/" },
  { title: "Ontology & Glossary", url: "/verlan/ontology/" },
  { title: "Current Trends", url: "/verlan/trends/" },
  { title: "Challenges & Solutions", url: "/verlan/challenges/" },
];

const keyPoints = [
  "Interactive verlan translator",
  "Practice quizzes with scoring",
  "Difficulty-based exercises",
  "Pronunciation guides",
];
---

<TopicLayout 
  title={title} 
  description={description}
  topic="Verlan"
  pillar="Tools & Resources"
  relatedTopics={relatedTopics}
  keyPoints={keyPoints}
>
  <h2>Interactive Learning Tools</h2>

  <p>This page serves as your gateway to practical verlan learning resources. Whether you're a French learner seeking to understand authentic speech, a linguist studying language games, or simply curious about French slang, these tools provide hands-on engagement with verlan mechanics and vocabulary.</p>

  <h2>Available Tools</h2>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
    <div style="background: #f8f7f5; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e8e6e0;">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">🔄 Verlan Translator</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Convert French words to their verlan equivalents and back. Includes a database of common terms and attempts algorithmic transformation for new words.</p>
      <a href="/tools/verlan-translator/" style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; background: #2b2b2b; color: white; text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 0.85rem;">Launch Translator →</a>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #f8f7f5; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e8e6e0;">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">📝 Verlan Quiz</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Test your knowledge with multiple-choice quizzes organized by difficulty level. Track your progress and identify areas for improvement.</p>
      <a href="/tools/verlan-quiz/" style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; background: #2b2b2b; color: white; text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 0.85rem;">Start Quiz →</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Learning Resources</h2>

  <h3>Beginner's Path</h3>

  <p>If you're new to verlan, we recommend this learning sequence:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Start with the <a href="/verlan/">Overview</a></strong> - Understand what verlan is and how it works conceptually</li>
    <li><strong>Learn high-frequency terms</strong> - Focus on common words like "meuf," "relou," and "ouf" before attempting complex formations</li>
    <li><strong>Practice recognition</strong> - Use the <a href="/tools/verlan-quiz/">quiz tool</a> to build your recognition vocabulary</li>
    <li><strong>Study the <a href="/verlan/ontology/">glossary</a></strong> - Reference the ontology for systematic vocabulary building</li>
    <li><strong>Explore authentic media</strong> - Listen to French hip-hop, watch contemporary films with verlan-heavy dialogue</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Intermediate Study</h3>

  <p>Once you have basic recognition, deepen your understanding:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Read the <a href="/verlan/technical-deep-dive/">Technical Deep-Dive</a></strong> - Understand the phonological mechanisms</li>
    <li><strong>Practice with the <a href="/tools/verlan-translator/">translator</a></strong> - Try predicting verlan forms before checking</li>
    <li><strong>Study regional variations</strong> - Note how verlan differs across French-speaking regions</li>
    <li><strong>Learn register awareness</strong> - Understand which terms are appropriate in which contexts</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Advanced Resources</h3>

  <p>For linguists and serious students:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/verlan/history/">Historical analysis</a></strong> - Trace verlan's evolution from 19th-century roots to present</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/verlan/trends/">Current research</a></strong> - Examine contemporary developments and future directions</li>
    <li><strong>Primary sources</strong> - Analyze verlan in French hip-hop lyrics, cinema, and literature</li>
  </ul>

